To install Ansible tower in rhel 8 
https://infotechys.com/install-ansible-tower-on-rhel-9/  -- This KB help to install the anisble tower
To download the specific version for ansible tower use below KB
https://releases.ansible.com/ansible-tower/setup/

Requirment for ansible tower:
https://docs.ansible.com/ansible-tower/latest/html/quickinstall/prepare.html#installation-and-reference-guide

1) Need to install ansible on server
2) DO not update the server, do not install python
2) sudo dnf install -y git wget 
3) ansible-galaxy collection install community.general  -- optional 
4) Get the file from the Document from laptop and unzip in the server.
5) ANSIBLE_BECOME=true ./setup.sh
In running installation it will give you insufficient RAM issue please use below KB to resolve the issue
https://bakingclouds.com/resolve-error-occurred-while-running-ansible-tower-installation/

6) After successfull installation you will not get site on the browser for that use below KB to resolve the issue.
https://www.devopsschool.com/forum/d/440-ansible-tower-access-issues/2  -- use 2nd method

Below step make the site up and running. 

    1  hostnamectl
    2  sudo dnf install ansible
    3  sudo dnf install ansible
    4  sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config
    sudo alternatives --set python /usr/bin/python3.12
    5  sudo passwd
    6  sudo systemctl restart sshd
    7  sudo passwd
    8  sudo passwd ec2-user
    9  ls -l
   10  sudo dnf install -y git wget
   11  python3
   12  sudo dnf install unzip
   13  unzip ansible-tower-setup-3.8.6-2.zip ;
   14  ls -l
   15  cd ansible-tower-setup-3.8.6-2
   16  vi inventory
   17  ANSIBLE_BECOME=true ./setup.sh
   18  cd /etc/tower/
   19  ls -l
   20  mv tower.cert tower.cert.old
   21  sudo mv tower.cert tower.cert.old
   22  sudo mv tower.key tower.key.old
   23  sudo openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048     -keyout /etc/tower/tower.key     -out /etc/tower/tower.crt     -subj "/CN=54.209.103.255"     -addext "keyUsage = digitalSignature, keyEncipherment"     -addext "extendedKeyUsage = serverAuth"
   24  sudo vi /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
   25  sudo systemctl restart nginx
   26  sudo systemctl restart ansible-tower
   27  python
   28  history



New command

    1  sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config
    2  sudo passwd ex2-user
    3  sudo passwd ec2-user
    4  sudo systemctl restart sshd
    5  sudo dnf install python3.12
    6  python --version
    7  which python
    8  sudo alternatives --set python /usr/bin/python3.12
    9  python
   10  whoch python
   11  which python
   12  sudo dnf install ansible
   13  sudo dnf install python3.12-pip
   14  sudo pip3 list
   15  sudo pip3.12 list
   16  ls -l
   17  hsi
   18  pip3.12  install ansible
   19  ansible --version
   20  history


sudo dnf install ansible
sudo dnf install -y git wget unzip zip
unzip ansible-tower-setup-3.8.6-2-new.zip
ANSIBLE_BECOME=true ./setup.sh
ANSIBLE_BECOME=true ./setup.sh -b  -- Backup ansible-tower
ANSIBLE_BECOME=true ./setup.sh -r  -- resotre the ansible-tower


Install tower-cli and use cli to create the resources.

   50  sudo dnf install python3 python3-pip
   51  pip install ansible-tower-cli
   52  pip3 install ansible-tower-cli
   53  sudo pip3 install ansible-tower-cli
   54  tower-cli job launch --help
   55  ls -al
   56  tower-cli config
   57  tower-cli config verify_ssl false
   58  tower-cli config
   59  ls -la
   60  vi .tower_cli.cfg
   61  tower-cli launch list
   62  tower-cli job_template list
   63  tower-cli config username admin
   64  tower-cli config password redhat
   65  tower-cli job_template list
   66  cat .tower_cli.cfg
   67  tower-cli user list
   68  tower-cli job_template list
   69  tower-cli job lunch --job-template=12
   70  tower-cli job launch --job-template=12
   71  tower-cli jon monitor 49
   72  tower-cli job monitor 49
   73  tower-cli job launch --job-template=12 --monitor
   74  tower-cli --help
   75  tower-cli workflow_job list
   76  tower-cli workflow list
   77  tower-cli job launch --job-template=13 --monitor
   78  tower-cli job launch --job-template=12 --monitor
   79  tower-cli workflow list


Use curl to get the api on ansible tower


   31  curl -k -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X GET --user admin:redhat localhost /api/v2/job_templates
   32  curl -k -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X GET --user admin:redhat localhost/api/v2/job_templates
   33  curl -k -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X GET --user admin:redhat localhost/api/v2/job_templates/
   34  curl -k -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X GET --user admin:redhat localhost/api/v2/job_templates/ | jq
